# AI Integration Rules

## Stack
- Provider: Vercel AI Gateway (unified endpoint, no per-provider API keys needed in code)
- SDK: AI SDK (the `ai` package from Vercel)
- Default model: `anthropic/claude-opus-4-6` — use for all complex reasoning tasks
- Fast model: `anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6` — use for quick, cheap tasks (category suggestions, short summaries)

## Decision Rule for Model Selection
Let the task complexity decide:
- Abstract summarizer → `claude-sonnet-4-6` (fast, cheap, straightforward)
- Category suggester → `claude-sonnet-4-6` (simple classification)
- Auto-score suggestions → `claude-opus-4-6` (reads full PDF, needs reasoning)
- School feedback report → `claude-opus-4-6` (nuanced, long-form writing)
- Results narrative report → `claude-opus-4-6` (multi-project synthesis)

## AI Client Setup (lib/ai.ts)
```ts
import { generateText, generateObject, streamText } from "ai"
import { z } from "zod"

// Vercel AI Gateway handles auth — no API key needed in code
// Models are referenced as "provider/model-name"

export const FAST_MODEL = "anthropic/claude-sonnet-4-6"
export const SMART_MODEL = "anthropic/claude-opus-4-6"
```

