## UI Components for AI Features

### AISuggestions.tsx (on scoring page)
- Show a collapsible panel: "✨ AI Suggestions"
- Display suggested score + justification per criterion
- "Apply" button next to each suggestion — clicking it moves the slider to that value
- Show loading skeleton while fetching
- If fetch fails, hide the panel silently — never block the judge from scoring

### AbstractSummary.tsx (on scoring page)
- Show above the full abstract as a highlighted box
- Label: "AI Summary"
- If `project.aiSummary` is null, show nothing

### CategorySuggester.tsx (on submission form)
- Appears after teacher types title + abstract (debounced 800ms)
- Shows: "💡 Suggested category: [name] — [reason]"
- "Use this" button auto-selects the category in the dropdown

## General AI Rules
- NEVER auto-submit scores based on AI suggestions — human judge must confirm
- NEVER show AI suggestions as "correct" — label them clearly as suggestions
- Always cache AI outputs in the DB — never re-run the same generation twice for the same project
- If an AI call fails, log the error and degrade gracefully — never crash the UI
- Stream responses for feedback generation (it's long) — use `streamText` not `generateText`
- All AI calls that require auth must verify Clerk session before calling the model
